'''irssi''' is a command line IRC client which allows you to connect to an internet relay chat (IRC) network.
== Install ==

{{USEflag|package=net-irc/irssi
|ipv6+yes+yes
|perl++yes
|socks5
|ssl+yes+yes
}}

install {{package|net-irc/irssi}}:

{{emerge|irssi}}
To run the program, simply open up a terminal and type 'irssi'. Read 'man irssi' to see all command line options.

==Configuring irssi==
The first time you run irssi a configuration file will be created for you in $HOME/.irssi/config.<br />
This can be modified with the /set command while in the client by typing '/set option value', type '/set' by it self to see all available options & their current value.
If you want your changes to stick over restarts, you will need to modify the configuration file for your irssi client.

== Using irssi ==
{{Cmd|irssi}}

* Connect to a IRC network, here irc.freenode.net
/connect irc.freenode.net

* set a user name f.e. larry
/nick larry

* Join a IRC channel f.e. #gentoo
/join #gentoo

* leave a channel
/leave #gentoo

* save configured irssi settings
/save

* quit irssi IRC session
/exit

